{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{infobox person |birth_date = {{birth date|1973|2|7}} |image = Boyan Petrov (cropped head shot).jpg |caption = Boyan Petrov, 2017 |disappeared_date = {{disappeared date and age|2018|5|5|1973|2|7}} |disappeared_place = Nyalam County, Tibet, China |disappeared_status = {{missing for|2018|5|5}} |nationality = [[Bulgarians|Bulgarian]] |known_for = Climbing 10 out of the 14 eight-thousanders without supplementary oxygen |occupation = Mountaineer, zoologist }} '''Boyan Petrov''' ({{lang-bg|Боян Петров}}, born 7 February 1973 - disappeared May 2018<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2018/05/16/krai-na-operaciiata-boian-ostava-zavinagi-pod-shisha-pangma.376595|title=Край на операцията... Боян остава завинаги под Шиша Пангма! {{!}} Dnes.bg|access-date=2018-08-12|language=bg}}</ref>) was a [[Bulgarians|Bulgarian]] [[zoologist]] and [[mountaineer]], working at the [[National Museum of Natural History (Bulgaria)|National Museum of Natural History]] in [[Sofia]].<ref name="npnm">[http://www.nmnhs.com/petrov-boyan-en.html Boyal Petrov], NMNHS</ref>
At the time of his disappearance he had climbed 10 out of the 14 [[eight-thousander]]s, all without supplementary oxygen. Up to date, this achievement makes him the Bulgarian altitude climber with the highest number of successful ascents of peaks over 8000 meters. He was the first Bulgarian to summit four of those mountains - [[Gasherbrum I]] (2009), [[Kangchenjunga]] (2014), [[K2]] (2014) and [[Manaslu]] (2015).
==Achievements== On 20 May 2014 he became the first Bulgarian to climb the third highest peak on Earth [[Kangchenjunga]] (8586m), as well as the first [[diabetes|diabetic]] to ascend to such an altitude and without oxygen.<ref>[http://www.monitor.bg/article?id=431481 Тайнствен глас водил Боян Петров към върха] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213225235/http://www.monitor.bg/article?id=431481 |date=13 December 2014 }}, Монитор</ref><ref>[http://www.novinite.com/articles/160731/Bulgarian+Mountaineer+Boyan+Petrov+Climbs+Kangchenjunga+Summit Bulgarian Mountaineer Boyan Petrov Climbs Kangchenjunga Summit]</ref> On 23 July he climbed [[Broad Peak]] (8047m).<ref name="BNR">[http://bnr.bg/en/post/100449432/boyan-petrov-the-most-successful-summer-of-bulgarian-mountaineering Boyan Petrov: The most successful summer of Bulgarian mountaineering], [[Bulgarian National Radio]]</ref> On 31 July 2014 he became the first Bulgarian to climb the second highest peak on the planet [[K2]] (8611m), which also made him the 35th person to climb three eight thousanders in less than 100 days.<ref>[http://offnews.bg/news/%D0%98%D0%BD%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B2%D1%8E_66/%D0%91%D0%BE%D1%8F%D0%BD-%D0%9F%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2-%D0%9D%D0%B0%D0%B9-%D0%B4%D0%BE%D0%B1%D1%80%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82-%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%BF%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%81%D1%82-%D0%B5-%D0%B6%D0%B8%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82-%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%BF%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%81%D1%82_425789.html Боян Петров: Най-добрият алпинист е живият алпинист] OFFNews</ref> His double climb – on Broad Peak and K2 in 8 days, is also a world record.<ref name="BNR"/> For these remarkable successes the Bulgarian climber was greeted with a video message by mountaineering legend [[Reinhold Messner]].<ref name="BNR"/> His documentary film about his climbs "3x8000" was broadcast on [[Bulgarian National Television]] in December 2014.<ref>[http://bnt.bg/about-bnt/presinformatsiya/bnt-izla-chva-vtora-chast-na-filma-3-x-8000 БНТ излъчва втора част на филма „3x8000“]</ref><ref>[http://www.cross.bg/boyan-filma-chast-1442721.html#axzz3LoUibgVo БНТ излъчва филм за алпиниста Боян Петров]</ref> He reached the summit of Mt. [[Dhaulagiri]] (8167m) on 29 September 2017 at 01:00 pm without the help of supplementary oxygen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreamwanderlust.com/news/bulgarian-mountaineer-boyan-petrov-summited-dhaulagiri-without-oxygen|title=Bulgarian mountaineer Boyan Petrov summited Dhaulagiri without Oxygen|date=2 October 2017|work=dreamwanderlust.com}}</ref>
Boyan Petrov was a [[cancer survivor]] and a [[Diabetes mellitus|diabetic]].<ref>Гергана Лабова, [http://www.gnezdoto.net/vdyhnovenie/762-boyan-petrov-jiv-si-kogato-ne-se-otkazvash "Боян Петров: жив си, когато не се отказваш"], www.gnezdoto.net, 2015, in Bulgarian. Retrieved 28-07-2016.</ref> In 2008 he fell while climbing in the [[Alps]] and broke his leg.<ref name="blitz.bg">Мара Калчева, [http://www.blitz.bg/article/34470 "Боян Петров: Диабетик съм, но катеря осемхилядници!"], www.blitz.bg, 28-05-2013, in Bulgarian. Retrieved 28-07-2016.</ref> During the descent of [[Gasherbrum II]] in 2009 he fell in a glacial [[crevasse]] and was saved by a group of Spanish climbers.<ref>Бойко Оков, [http://www.verticalworld.net/articles/article.php?id=354 "Покорителят на Гашербрум -1 и Гашербрум - 2 Боян Петров: Бях сам, спикел и щека на 30 метра от върха"], www.verticalworld.net, 28-08-2009, in Bulgarian. Retrieved 28-07-2016.</ref> In 2013 Petrov suffered another leg fracture due to a car accident.<ref name="blitz.bg"/> Despite his injuries, in the following year he achieved a hat-trick by successfully climbing [[Kangchenjunga]], [[Broad Peak]] and [[K2]] with [[Internal fixation|internal fixators]] in this leg.<ref>Бойко Оков, [http://www.blitz.bg/news/article/285365 "Властелинът на осемхилядниците покорил К2 с 12 пирона в крака"], www.blitz.bg, 17-08-2014, in Bulgarian. Retrieved 28-07-2016.</ref> After the descent of K2, he suffered a serious [[Diabetic hypoglycemia|hypoglycemic crisis]] while in base camp, lost consciousness and was able to recover with the help of Polish climbers.<ref>Michał Bugno, [http://sport.wp.pl/kat,137874,title,Dziekuja-Polakom-za-uratowanie-czlowieka-na-Broad-Peak-To-bohaterstwo,wid,16878465,wiadomosc.html?ticaid=117728 "Dziękują Polakom za uratowanie człowieka na Broad Peak. "To bohaterstwo!"], sport.wp.pl, 12-09-2014, in Polish. Retrieved 28-07-2016.</ref><ref>Стефан Чолаков, [https://www.24chasa.bg/Article/4245141 "Боян Петров: Под К-2 имах криза заради кръвната захар"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816182432/https://www.24chasa.bg/Article/4245141 |date=16 August 2016 }}, "24 часа", 14-08-2014, in Bulgarian. Retrieved 28-07-2016.</ref>
==Disappearance== {{expand section|date=May 2018}} Petrov was declared missing on 5 May 2018 while climbing [[Shishapangma]]. The search for him was discontinued on 16 May.<ref>[http://www.dreamwanderlust.com/news/the-final-report-puts-to-rest-all-speculations-surrounding-the-boyan-petrov-search-operation "The final report puts to rest all speculations surrounding the Boyan Petrov Search Operation"], "Dream Wanderlust", 17.05.2018.</ref> According to other climbers, he may have fallen into a crevasse on the way to the top.<ref>{{cite web |title=Boyan Petrov's Team: The Rescue Operation is Over |url=http://www.novinite.com/articles/190127/Boyan+Petrov%27s+Team%3A+The+Rescue+Operation+is+Over |publisher=Novinite.xom |date=16 May 2018 |accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref>
