'''Parathyroiditis''' is a condition involving inflammation of the [[parathyroid gland]].

It can be associated with [[hyperparathyroidism]],<ref name="pmid9227385">{{cite journal |vauthors=Vaizey CJ, Ali M, Gilbert JM |title=Chronic parathyroiditis associated with primary hyperplastic hyperparathyroidism |journal=J R Soc Med |volume=90 |issue=6 |pages=336–7 |date=June 1997 |pmid=9227385 |pmc=1296314 |doi= |url=}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Lloyd|first1=Ricardo V.|title=Endocrine Pathology:: Differential Diagnosis and Molecular Advances|date=2010|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=9781441910691|page=150|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Je9QTWRH6s8C&dq=Parathyroiditis&source=gbs_navlinks_s|accessdate=19 December 2017|language=en}}</ref> though most cases are asymptomatic.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Erickson|first1=Lori A.|title=Atlas of Endocrine Pathology|date=2014|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=9781493904433|page=106|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n1G-BAAAQBAJ&dq=Parathyroiditis&source=gbs_navlinks_s|accessdate=19 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>

