'''Selibi Phikwe Government Hospital''' is a [[government hospital|government-run]] [[Hospital#District|district hospital]] located in [[Selebi Phikwe]],is a mining [[List of cities in Botswana|town]] located in the [[Central District (Botswana)|Central District]] of [[Botswana]]. It had a population of 49,849 in 2001 which is now estimated to have risen to c.52000.<ref>[http://www.laws.gov.bw/ Laws of Botswana], [http://www.mlg.gov.bw/ Ministry of Local Government] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090718061659/http://www.mlg.gov.bw/ |date=2009-07-18 }}</ref>
== History == Selibi Phikwe Government Hospital is a Government health institution founded in 1970. The institution is located at the central district of [[Botswana]] in a town called [[Selebi Phikwe]].
