{{Infobox person | name = Stephen Crohn | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Stephen Lyon Crohn | birth_date = {{birth date|mf=yes|1946|9|5}} | birth_place = [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2013|8|23|1946|9|5}} | death_place = Manhattan, New York City | death_cause = [[Suicide methods#Drug overdose|Suicide by drug overdose]] | alma_mater = | occupation = Chef | years_active = | employer = | boards = | awards = | website = <!-- {{URL|}} --> }} '''Stephen Lyon Crohn''' (September 5, 1946 – August 23, 2013)<ref name="nyt crohn">{{cite web|author=John Schwartz| title=Stephen Crohn, Who Furthered AIDS Study, Dies at 66| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/09/15/health/stephen-crohn-who-furthered-aids-study-dies-at-66.html?_r=1&| publisher=The New York Times| date=September 14, 2013|accessdate=September 16, 2013}}</ref> also known as "The man who can't catch [[AIDS]]", was a man notable for a [[genetic mutation]], which caused him to be [[HIV immunity|immune]] to AIDS. He was a great-nephew of [[Burrill Bernard Crohn]], for whom [[Crohn's disease]] is named.<ref>http://www.woodstockx.com/2013/09/20/in-memoriam-steve-crohn/</ref>
Crohn had the [[CCR5#CCR5-.CE.9432|"delta 32"]] mutation on the [[CCR5]] receptor,<ref name="indp crohn">{{cite web|author=Tom Wilkie|title=The man who can't catch AIDS|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/the-man-who-cant-catch-aids-1344588.html|publisher=The Independent|date=September 16, 2013 |accessdate=September 16, 2013}}</ref><ref name="pbs crohn">{{cite web|author=NOVA (PBS airdate: February 2, 1999) |title=Surviving AIDS|url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/nova/transcripts/2603aids.html |publisher=NOVA (PBS)|date=February 2, 1999|accessdate=September 16, 2013}}</ref><ref name="mail crohn">{{cite web|author=Helen Pow|title=The 'man who couldn't get AIDS' commits suicide at 66 out of 'survivors guilt' decades after VOLUNTEERING to be injected with HIV|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2421699/Stephen-Crohn-dies-man-AIDS-commits-suicide-66-survivors-guilt.html|publisher=Mail Online|date=September 15, 2013|accessdate=September 16, 2013|location=United Kingdom}}</ref> a [[protein]] on the surface of [[white blood cells]] that is involved in the [[immune system]] and serves as an access route for many forms of HIV virus to enter and infect host cells. This mutation rendered him effectively immune to many forms of HIV.
==Death== Crohn committed suicide by a drug overdose on [[oxycodone]] and [[benzodiazepine]]s at the age of 66.<ref name="herld crohn">{{cite web|author=News Limited Network|title=The man who couldn't catch AIDS, Stephen Crohn, dies from suicide aged 66|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/lifestyle/health-fitness/the-man-who-couldnt-catch-aids-stephen-crohn-dies-from-suicide-aged-66/story-fni0dgux-1226719799380|publisher=Herald Sun|date=September 16, 2013|accessdate=September 16, 2013|location=Australia }}</ref><ref name="nyma_TheM">{{Cite web| title = The Man Who Was Immune to AIDS| author = Jesse Green| work = NYMag.com| date = 2014-06-13| accessdate = 2015-01-20| url =http://nymag.com/health/bestdoctors/2014/steve-crohn-aids-2014-6/}}</ref>
